statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from `products` where exists (select * from `categories` inner join `products_categories` on `categories`.`id` = `products_categories`.`category_id` where `products`.`id` = `products_categories`.`product_id` and `categories`.`deleted_at` is null) and exists (select * from `brands` where `products`.`brand_id` = `brands`.`id` and `brands`.`deleted_at` is null) and `products`.`deleted_at` is null

select * from `products` where exists (select * from `categories` inner join `products_categories` on `categories`.`id` = `products_categories`.`category_id` where `products`.`id` = `products_categories`.`product_id` and `categories`.`deleted_at` is null) and exists (select * from `brands` where `products`.`brand_id` = `brands`.`id` and `brands`.`deleted_at` is null) and `products`.`deleted_at` is null order by `id` desc limit 20 offset 0

select `categories`.*, `products_categories`.`product_id` as `pivot_product_id`, `products_categories`.`category_id` as `pivot_category_id` from `categories` inner join `products_categories` on `categories`.`id` = `products_categories`.`category_id` where `products_categories`.`product_id` in (1, 3) and `categories`.`deleted_at` is null
select * from `brands` where `brands`.`id` in (1) and `brands`.`deleted_at` is null
select * from `users` where `name` is null limit 1
